Subject: [Bioc-devel] Author/maintainer field no longer accepted.
In-Reply-To: <1ADF56D9-4E8D-4A15-981E-A19EAAABD525@prinsesmaximacentrum.nl>
References: <1ADF56D9-4E8D-4A15-981E-A19EAAABD525@prinsesmaximacentrum.nl>
Message-ID: <700F1A41-51B2-443F-8688-091F409ED1E9@prinsesmaximacentrum.nl>

Hi All,

R BiocCheck no longer seems to accept a Author/Maintainer field. (https://github.com/Bioconductor/BiocCheck/commit/e0176f6591c771774f6cb05d4ff8bc1b145ad10e)

* Checking for valid maintainer...
    * ERROR: Remove Maintainer field. Use Authors at R [cre] designation.

However, the package guidelines (https://www.bioconductor.org/developers/package-guidelines/) still say that a Author/Maintainer field is allowed:
Authors at R or Author/Maintainer:? fields: Use either Authors at R field or Author: and Maintainer: fields, not both.

I think the guidelines need to be updated.

With kind regards,
Freek Manders


